The accelerometer records dynamic or static forces the sensor is experiencing in x,y, and z directions. The acceleration probe reading consists of x, y, and z axes, which specify the axes’ acceleration. In this study, tri-axis readings were considered for feature extraction. From the raw three-axis accelerometer data, which was taken at 1800 samples per hour, the accelerometer magnitude was computed using (1). Further arithmetic mean of accelerometer magnitude was also computed from the accelerometer readings [27, 28].
